Package mms.storage

Class Box

Object
Storage
Box
All Implemented Interfaces:
Packable
public class Box extends Storage implements Packable
A box to store different items in.
Boxes can be marked as fragile and have comments about their contents.

A box contains fragile items if it contains either a television or laptop. If a box does not contain these items then it is not considered fragile.

Implement this for Assignment 1

    • toString

      public String toString()
      Returns the human-readable string representation of the box.

      The format of the string to return is: 

      Box ('width', 'height', 'length') size - 'comment'

      Where:

      • 'width' is this box's width in cm.
      • 'height' is this box's height in cm.
      • 'length' is this box's length in cm.
      • 'size' is this box's size.
      • 'comment' is this box's comment. If the box is fragile then the string " FRAGILE" must be appended to the comment.
        If the box's comment is an empty string then the string "'\0'" should be displayed instead.

      The box's width, height and length should be formatted to two decimal places.

      For example: 

      Box (5.6, 5.6, 5) MEDIUM - Kitchenware
      Overrides:
      toString in class Storage
      Returns:
      string representation of this box

    • pack

      public void pack(Packable item) throws PackingException
      Description copied from class: Storage
      Adds an item to the storages internal list.

      If the storage is at capacity or adding the item to this storage causes any 2 of the sum of the elements' width, height or length to be greater than the width, height or length (respectively) of this storage than an exception should be thrown and no action should be taken.
      That is, exceeding one sum is ok but exceeding 2 should cause an exception.

      This method declares to throw a PackingException to allow subclasses to throw additional exceptions to the same type.

      Overrides:
      pack in class Storage
      Parameters:
      item - the item to add to the list
      Throws:
      StorageFullException - if the current elements size >= the capacity of this storage or if two of the following are true:
      ∑ widths of items in the storage + width of new item > storage width,
      ∑ heights of items in the storage + height of new item > storage height,
      ∑ lengths of items in the storage + length of new item > storage length
      PackingException
